I would never EVER want liverpool to sign a ready made superstar. For me that would just ruin the balance and dynamics of the whole team! What makes us great is that every single player comes in knowing that they have to put in the work!
For example the links with Mbappe and Sancho etc.. most fans would love it if we signed them, I wouldn't! I'd rather stick with the guys who fight for our badge every single game! The guys who have won us the champions league and on their way to the premier league! Why look elsewhere when we have the best right in front of our eyes😎❤

snippet.textDisplay:
Might sound stupid, but I think as soon as they switch to the Nike kit, shits gonna go wrong.
if it ain't broke, don't "fix" it.
New-balance is not a hugely popular brand, means you throw your kit on and you go out there and play.
Make the biggest UK kit signing with Nike, and all the players are gonna start thinking they've got it easy now, biggest brand, because we're the best, then turns into less effort put into the game.
I know it sounds retarded, but little things can make a huge difference.

If I were them I'd have stuck with NB. Man U and Chelsea both switched from Nike and Adidas to the other, and they've not been too hot the last few years. Keep things the same.
